<figureCitation id="13042A060D20FFF0C018C37B82C8E24B" box="[793,928,852,878]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[136,229,1734,1756]" captionStartId-1="3.[136,229,1551,1573]" captionStartId-2="4.[136,229,2066,2088]" captionTargetBox-0="[204,1386,187,1677]" captionTargetBox-1="[312,1275,190,1527]" captionTargetId-0="figure-21@2.[201,1386,187,1707]" captionTargetId-1="figure-17@3.[312,1275,190,1527]" captionTargetId-2="figure-156@4.[295,1293,631,2042]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Vochysia sobralii. A. Flowering branch. B. Nodal region, showing stipules. C. Detail of the indument on the abaxial surface of the leaf. D. Flower in lateral view. E. Flower in front view. F. Stamen in front (left) and back (right) views. G. Gynoecium. H. Front view of flower after anthesis with the two frontal sepals and part of the hypanthium removed. I. Staminode. M. Sobral &amp; A.G. Oliveira 10876. Drawn by Klei Sousa." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Vochysia sobralii. A. Habit. B. Inflorescences. C. Detail of the inflorescence with flower buds on top, flowers in anthesis on the central portion and older flowers showing just the ovaries on the proximal portion of the inflorescence. D. Detail of open flowers with showy fourth sepal and curved style. E. Flower buds showing acute apex and recurved spur. F. Detail of old flowers, showing just the tomentose ovaries. A–F. M. Sobral &amp; A.G. Oliveira 10876. All photos by M. Sobral." captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Geographic distribution of Vochysia sobralii (red star)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417882" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417894" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417902" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6417882/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6417894/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6417902/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="208">Figures 1–3</figureCitation>
)
